There are only 8 new cases in China, and they have already reached zero. There were more than 8,000 new cases overseas, 1,000 times more than at home. The United States has been slow to respond; many countries in Europe have stepped up quarantine and restrictions on traffic

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Xu Jintu, data researcher at CAIJING | CAIJING Vision Center

Editor | Hao Zhou

There are only 8 new cases in China

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Summary of China Today: 80,813 confirmed cases were reported in China on March 12, with 8 new cases. There were 3 imported cases in non-hubei area, and no local cases. Hubei non-wuhan area for the 8th consecutive day zero new. The number of new cases in Wuhan dropped to 5 for the first time, and an additional case was suspected. In order to prevent "import" , the domestic ports of entry personnel screening, tracking, isolation efforts further increased.

The number of overseas cases has exceeded 50,000, an increase of 1,000 times that of domestic cases

Figure 1

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
More than 50,000 cases have been reported overseas, and the number of new cases has increased to 8,000 + in a single day. Affected by the outbreak, major stock indexes in the United States and Europe plunged, U. S. stocks for the second time in a week the fuse. International Oil and gold prices also fell.

United Nations headquarters in New York reported the first confirmed case on 12 March involving a female diplomat from the Philippine mission to the United Nations. Prime Minister Trudo's wife Sufi tested positive for the new coronavirus, the prime minister's office confirmed March 12 local time. Trudo, however, has no symptoms and is in good health.

Figure 2

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Europe has continued to grow, becoming a hard-hit area for overseas outbreaks. Many countries sounded the alarm and began tightening restrictions. See the European section for more details.

Third, the United States has been slow to respond and the outlook is grim

Figure 3

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the United States, 443 new cases were recorded today, reaching 1,754. There is no doubt that the number will exceed 2,000 tomorrow. Xiao Bian thinks that, american leaders still cling to two important judgments: 1) the disease is entirely foreign, first from China and now from Europe. He was reluctant to admit that the disease had been largely "endogenous" . 2) the so called epidemic, which is mainly a political phenomenon, is caused by the Democratic Party and the media. It would cause economic damage, and infectious diseases by themselves would be insignificant. So far his main prescriptions have been: first, refuting rumors and supporting the economy; Second, "Travel Ban" ; and third, by the way, please pay attention to hygiene, in case of infection mainly by calm "self-cure. ". Completely ignored the isolation, screening, treatment, tracking the work of such closed-loop prevention and control of infectious diseases. He sees the virus as a flea that can't be beaten. If 10 fingers deal with a flea every day, you can really calm down, or even accept as "normal. ". But if the fleas multiply rapidly, becoming 100 in two weeks, 10,000 in four weeks, and a million in six weeks, it's hard to be calm. And that's exactly what the virus in front of us is capable of. Given that more than 10 percent of new cases will be critical in seven weeks than there are beds in the United States, that would be a disaster. The United States, however, is slow to respond

It's all in the ballpark. There's almost no deviation. At this rate, without adequate intervention, the number of cases will be over a million in 25 days. It's important to note that multiple sources and multiple sources suggest that the current U.S. data are understated or even severely understated. Small series according to this can draw the conclusion: again do not take action, the prospect is unimaginable!

IV. European measures to strengthen isolation and restriction of movement

Figure 4

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Europe is still in the outbreak phase, has not yet reached the peak. Countries have tightened quarantine and flow-limiting measures.

British Prime Minister Johnson said March 12, will take all measures to control the epidemic, the epidemic peak will be delayed for weeks. Valence, the UK's chief scientific adviser, said there could be between 5,000 and 10,000 people infected locally, based on the 590 confirmed cases so far, putting the trajectory of the epidemic about four weeks behind Italy, he expects the UK to peak in 10 to 14 weeks.

French President Maqueron says the country is at the beginning of the crisis, with schools across the country suspended indefinitely from Monday.

The Belgian government announced that all cultural and entertainment venues and restaurants would be temporarily closed from midnight on March 13 until April 3, and that schools would be closed for five weeks, although supermarkets and pharmacies would remain open.

For the first time, Spain has declared a siege. IGUALADA, a village in Northern Catalonia, and three nearby villages have been cordoned off.

Portugal has also decided to suspend classes until April 9, closing nightclubs, restricting the number of shopping malls and restaurants, and allowing only Portuguese citizens to land on local cruise ships.

Figure 5

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Italy... is still miserable. Italy joined the list after Germany seized Swiss defence supplies and allegedly seized a shipment of disinfectant from Switzerland.

5. South Korea says the economic situation is unusually grim

Figure 6

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Economic activity and market psychology are depressed and uncertainties in the real economy and financial markets have increased as a result of the new crown epidemic, the Ministry of Planning and Finance said in its March 13 issue of the latest economic trends. The impact of the new crown epidemic was evident in February's consumer data, with Chinese visitors to South Korea down 76.1 per cent, the biggest drop since statistics began in January 1999. Sales at discount stores fell 19.6 per cent, the biggest drop since January 2015, while department store sales fell 30.6 per cent. South Korean President Moon jae-in also said after hearing a report on economic developments that the current economic situation is exceptionally severe and that it is an exceptional time that can not be compared with the Middle East during SARS and SARS.

6. Iran's foreign minister, Zarif, calls for help after 10,000 confirmed cases

Figure 7

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Iran has more than 10,000 confirmed cases. Iran's foreign minister, Zarif, posted a plea for help on the social networking site on March 12, listing the supplies Iran needs, including 3.2 million kits for testing for the virus, 12 million N95 masks, 1, 100 million pairs of disposable medical gloves and so on. Zarif noted the country's difficulties in facing severe shortages, writing that "viruses do not discriminate and humans should not. "

[ special note: The above statistics, for the WHO official statistics before February 28, the data cut-off time is 17:00 China Standard Time; starting from February 28, the data from the "CAIJING" according to public statistics, the cut-off time is 9:00 China Standard Time. ]

7. Quick overview of the global epidemic:

[60 seconds ] on March 13, Chinese company Alibaba Cloud announced it would offer free cloud-based virus-matching services to medical research institutions, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and other front-line virus research institutions around the world, it can greatly improve the efficiency of virus gene detection, and complete the gene comparison of any virus including the new coronavirus in 60 seconds at the earliest, providing effective basis for further understanding of virus mutation.

The world's 500 richest people lost a combined $331 billion in the March 13 stock market crash, the biggest one-day drop in the eight-year history of the Bloomberg Billionaires Index. Since the beginning of 2020, the combined net worth of the 500 richest people has lost 16 percent to $950 billion, according to the Bloomberg Billionaires Index.

3. [ tracking 16,000 people ] the Ministry of Health said on March 13 that during a rally at the 2012 Malaysian Open  Doubles Mosque in Jamek Sri Petaling from February 28 to March 1, dozens of people have been diagnosed as directly or indirectly infected with NCP. As the 16,000 people attending the rally are at risk of infection, the Malaysian government has launched a close tracking of the participants.

On March 12, the Australian government announced a total of a $17.6 billion (77.58 billion yuan) in response to the outbreak, this includes a one-off payment of 750 Australian dollars (3,306 yuan) to more than 6 million welfare recipients, including retirees and the unemployed, from March 31. In addition, the government will subsidise the wages of 120,000 apprentices and provide assistance to smes up to a $25,000(about $110,000) .

Summary: There are only 8 new cases in China, and they have already returned to zero. More than 8,000 new cases have been reported overseas, 1,000 times as many as at home. The US response has been slow, with multiple sources and multiple lines of evidence pointing to an underestimation of the current US figures and a very negative outlook. Many countries in Europe have stepped up their measures of isolation and restriction of traffic.
